Package gtsoft.ivory.server.jca.cci

Interface Summary
IvoryRecord The IvoryRecord interface is implemented by all Ivory*Record classes.
 

Class Summary
IvoryBaseRecord This abstract class is the superclass of all Ivory supplied classes which act as a javax.resource.cci.Record used to pass data to and from the Ivory resource adapter.
IvoryCallableServicesRecord This class is used for exchanging request and response data with the Ivory resource adapter for callable services processing.
IvoryConnectionSpec Base class for IvoryLocalConnectionSpec and IvoryRemoteConnectionSpec.
IvoryDomDocumentRecord This class is used for exchanging request and response data with the Ivory resource adapter.
IvoryInteractionSpec Use an IvoryInteractionSpec object as the first parameter to Interaction.execute.
IvoryJDomDocumentRecord This class is used for exchanging request and response data with the Ivory resource adapter.
IvoryLocalConnectionSpec Use an IvoryLocalConnectionSpec object as the parameter to ConnectionFactory.getConnection when the Ivory resource adapter will execute locally within the same application server as the invoking application.
IvoryRemoteConnectionSpec Use an IvoryRemoteConnectionSpec object as the parameter to ConnectionFactory.getConnection when the Ivory resource adapter is to communicate with a remote Ivory Server using http or https.
IvoryStringRecord This class is used for exchanging request and response data with the Ivory resource adapter.
